# Context

Removing torEst and i from the feature set collapses MLP RMSE from 13.53 to 32.59 and GRU RMSE from 13.66 to 46.97 on the combined test set. This 8-feature configuration {torDes, posDes, velDes, posAct, posErr, velErr, velAct, accelAct} is the closest match to Hwangbo's "no direct torque telemetry" feature set and is the honest test of "can a NN learn actuator dynamics from kinematics alone."

Before drawing thesis-grade conclusions from a single training run, replicate the result, evaluate per-profile, and verify training was healthy.

# Task

1. Re-run the 8-feature training three times with different random seeds (existing v1 seed plus two new ones). Same hyperparameters as v1. Report mean ± std of RMSE/MAE across the three runs for both MLP and GRU. This quantifies the noise floor on the 32.59/46.97 numbers.

2. For the median-performing run of each architecture, evaluate per-profile (PLC, PMS, TMS, tStep) using the canonical baseline test split protocol (whichever was confirmed correct in Prompt 13's reconciliation).

