6. Compute Test 1 equivalent for the 8-feature setup: what's the RMSE of "predict zero" and "predict torDes" baselines on the same test split? If 8-feature MLP at 32 Nm beats predict-torDes by less than 3x, the kinematic features are providing weak lift over the trivial baseline.

# Interpretation

- "Result is robust": std across seeds < 2 Nm. The 32/47 numbers are real.
- "Result is unstable": std across seeds > 5 Nm. Need more seeds and possibly hyperparameter retuning.
- "Per-profile pattern preserved": if tStep/TMS RMSE rises proportionally on each profile and PLC stays similar, the leakage features were helping uniformly. If tStep RMSE rises 100x while PLC RMSE stays the same, the leakage features were specifically responsible for the easy-profile performance.
- "Kinematic features insufficient": if 8-ft MLP RMSE is within 3x of predict-torDes, the kinematic feature set genuinely cannot model HEJ-90 torque well.

